    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/684.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 340.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose to the Department
                    herewith in translation for its information copy of a letter<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d525fn1">Not printed.</note> from Gen. Villar, who is at present
                    operating in the northern part of the country, to President Diaz, in which he
                    complains somewhat bitterly of a fancied laxness of the American authorities
                    along the Texas border in permitting Mexican malcontents to carry on operations
                    of various kinds from the American side.</p>
                <p>During an interview with President Diaz a few days ago he expressed himself in
                    the same vein, intimating that a stricter patrol should be enforced and that the
                    governor of Texas should give the matter more careful attention.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
